-- Polish Stocks: Lotos, Orlen, Stalprodukt Are Active in Warsaw
-- B y   P i o t r   B u j n i c k i   a n d   M a r t a   W a l d o c h
-- 2012-01-18T16:49:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-18/polish-stocks-lotos-orlen-stalprodukt-are-active-in-warsaw.html
Poland’s  WIG20 Index (WIG20)  gained for a
third day, adding 20.22, or 0.9 percent, to 2,228.09 at the 5:30
p.m. close in Warsaw.  The following are among the most active stocks on the
Warsaw Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  PKN Orlen SA (PKN)  , Poland’s biggest oil company, rose
for a third day, climbing 3.4 percent to 37.03 zloty, and  Grupa
Lotos SA (LTS)  , the second-largest refiner, gained 4 percent
to 23.41 zloty. Oil advanced as U.S. industrial output rebounded
amid increasing tension between Iran and Saudi Arabia.  Bank Pekao SA (PEO)  , majority-owned by Italy’s UniCredit
SpA, rose 1.7 percent to 145.9 zloty, the highest this year, as
UBS AG raised its price estimate to 152 zloty per share from 151
zloty.  Stalprodukt SA (STP)  , the Polish steel-product maker,
slumped 2.9 percent to 265 zloty, falling from a one-month high.
ING Groep NV recommended selling the stock in new coverage with
a price estimate of 223 zloty.  To contact the reporters on this story:
